  pmid         = {27416071},
  issn         = {1932-6203},
  abstract     = {Stereotypic behavior is an important indicator of compromised
                  welfare. Zoo elephants are documented to perform stereotypic
                  behavior, but the factors that contribute to performance have
                  not been systematically assessed. We collected behavioral data
                  on 89 elephants (47 African [Loxodonta africana], 42 Asian
